  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It is a criminal offense that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by processing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. The purpose is to make the money appear as if it comes from a legitimate source.\n\nMoney laundering is often associated with other criminal activities, such as drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, and terrorism financing. Laws and regulations aimed at preventing money laundering require financial institutions and other businesses to monitor and report suspicious activities to authorities. Penalties for money laundering can be severe, including hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
